{{Infobox census | name = Fifth Census of Pakistan | logo = | logo_size = | logo_caption = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | country = Pakistan | date = {{start date|1998|||df=y}} | population = 132,352,000 | percent_change = {{gain}} | annual_percent_change = | region_type = province/territory | most_populous = [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]] | least_populous = [[Islamabad Capital Territory]] }}
The '''1998 Pakistan Census''' is a detailed enumeration of the [[Pakistani]] population held in 1998 by the [[Pakistan Bureau of Statistics]], an agency of the [[Government of Pakistan]].<ref>http://www.pbs.gov.pk/content/demographic-indicators-1998-census</ref> According to the 1998 census, the population of Pakistan was 130,857,717. With the inclusion of the population of [[Azad Kashmir|Azad Jammu & Kashmir]] and [[Gilgit-Baltistan]], the population was 134,714,017 in 1998.
