'''''Ecolibrium''''' is a [[The Sims|Sims]]-style game for the [[Play Station Vita|PS Vita]] with an [[Environmentalism|environmental]] message.<ref name=Highfield2012>{{cite news|last1=Highfield|first1=Vaughn|title=Ecolibrium review|url=http://www.pocketgamer.co.uk/r/PS+Vita/Ecolibrium/review.asp?c=45184|accessdate=21 June 2014|publisher=Pocketgamer UK|date=28 September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Morris|first1=Reagan|title=Ecolibrium Review|url=http://nzgamer.com/reviews/1735/ecolibrium.html|accessdate=21 June 2014|publisher=NZ Gamer|date=3 October 2012}}</ref> The player controls a virtual [[ecosystem]] in which to grow and care for [[flora]] and [[fauna]] by manipulating four variables - Water, Minerals, Vegetation, and Meat - in order to create a balanced ecosystem. The player gains and spends 'ecopoints' and also tackles a series of multi-stage challenges.<ref name=Highfield2012 /> ''Ecolibrium'' received "mixed" reviews, according to video game [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].<ref>http://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-vita/ecolibrium</ref>
